<HEADLINE>
<P>
JENKINS IS NAMED WEST BASEBALL COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Redondo High baseball Coach Harry Jenkins, who has been out of coaching 
for two years, has been named coach at West Torrance High. 
</P>
<P>
Jenkins guided Redondo to 10 league titles in 19 seasons at Redondo. He 
resigned to pursue business interests after the 1988 season, when the Sea Hawks 
went 30-3 and reached the CIF-Southern Section 4-A semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
Jenkins had intended to help Palos Verdes Coach Gil Eberhard this spring until 
West offered him a head coaching job. 
</P>
<P>
Jenkins replaces Dick McGrath, who resigned after coaching West for one season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111690-0026 </DOCNO>
