<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
WILD PIERCE COMEBACK FALLS SHORT IN WSC VOLLEYBALL SHOWDOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pierce College nearly overcame a two-game deficit before finally falling to 
Ventura in the Western State Conference women's volleyball tournament Thursday 
night at Moorpark College. 
</P>
<P>
Ventura beat Pierce, 15-7, 15-9, 3-15, 15-17, 15-10, in a match to determine 
WSC berths and seedings in the upcoming state tournament. 
</P>
<P>
The match was necessary because Pierce, Ventura and Cuesta tied for the 
conference championship with 16-2 records. 
</P>
<P>
Ventura (18-2), guaranteed a state tournament berth, will play Cuesta tonight 
at Santa Barbara City at 6 p.m. for the WSC's top seeding in the state 
playoffs. Pierce (17-3) will attempt to earn a wild-card berth and could enter 
the state tournament as the conference's third-seeded team. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Canyons 80, Rancho Santiago 46 -- Keira Irwin scored a career-high 21 points to 
lead four Canyons players in double figures in a first-round game of the Golden 
West tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark 81, Saddleback 72 -- Moorpark outscored Saddleback by 13 points in the 
second half to pull out a first-round victory in the Long Beach City College 
tournament. Lisa Huffaker led Moorpark with 17 points. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
MEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Antelope Valley 120, Canyons 94 -- Tony Madison scored 28 points to lead 
Antelope Valley (2-0) to an easy nonconference victory at home. 
</P>
<P>
Oxnard 93, Harbor 90 (2 OTs) -- Greg Hernandez was five for six at the 
free-throw line and grabbed three offensive rebounds in overtime for Oxnard 
(3-0) in the opening round of the Compton tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Shawn Talley scored a game-high 28 points, Don Mitchell had 22 and Tim Thomas 
15 for Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
Ventura 94, Edwards AFB 86 -- Lester Neal had 23 points and 16 rebounds and Uba 
Satterfield added 22 points and 11 rebounds to pace Ventura (2-0) in the first 
round of the Cypress tournament. 
</P>
