<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Murder on Mock Trial: A group of well-known actors took part in a mock trial 
staged this morning outside the Federal Building in downtown Los Angeles to 
commemorate the anniversary of the murder of six Jesuit priests in El Salvador. 
</P>
<P>
The organization, called the Wednesday Morning Coalition for Peace and Justice 
in Central America and the U.S., will "try" the murderers of the six priests, 
their cook and her daughter in a street opera featuring masked actors, puppets 
and mimes. Among those scheduled to participate were actors Martin Sheen, Ed 
Asner and Robert Foxworth. The eight were fatally shot on Nov. 16, 1989, at the 
University of Central America in San Salvador. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
