outbreak of anti-government sentiment since last December's uprising. The 
protests in Bucharest, above, and other large cities were the result of a 
government decree allowing producers to set prices according to what the market 
will bear, while wages remain fixed. Agence France-Presse; Photo, (Orange 
County Edition) "We fight! We work! We starve!" demonstrators chant in 
Transylvanian city of Brasov, Romania. Associated Press 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
<SUBJECT>
