<HEADLINE>
<P>
VILLAGERS TURN OUT TO VOTE FOR BUNCH OF TURKEYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANCHORAGE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Residents of the village of Koliganek cast their votes last week and came up 
with a bunch of turkeys. 
</P>
<P>
The villagers have been declared the winners of $500 worth of turkeys in a 
contest, sponsored by the Bristol Bay Native Assn., to encourage the region's 
residents to vote. Seventy of Koliganek's 87 registered voters, or 80.5%, 
participated on Nov. 6, said association director Terry Hoefferle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
