<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: COLLEGE STUDENTS PROTEST CANCELLATION OF 
CONCERT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than 150 Occidental College students staged a daylong sit-in Thursday at 
the Eagle Rock campus after administrators canceled a free rap concert and 
graffiti art show organized by student minority groups and fraternities. 
</P>
<P>
Eleven student groups and several community activists had invited high school 
students throughout Los Angeles to the college's outdoor amphitheater Friday 
night to hear four rap groups, watch graffiti artists doing demonstrations and 
visit information tables set up by ethnic organizations. 
</P>
<P>
Dean of Students Brigida Knauer on Tuesday canceled the concert, saying she was 
concerned about potential gang fights and lack of security. Knauer said she 
initially approved the event, but changed her mind after learning that many 
more high school students had been invited than was expected. 
</P>
</TEXT>
