<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: YOUTH CHARGED IN DELGADO SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Hawthorne teen-ager was charged with murder Wednesday in the shooting death 
of Leuzinger High School student Robert Delgado, 16, who had recently joined a 
gang, a spokeswoman with the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Information Bureau 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old suspect, whose name was withheld because he is a juvenile, had 
been suspended from Leuzinger High School for fighting but returned to campus 
Nov. 5 and became embroiled in a fight with Delgado, Deputy Britta Rodela said. 
</P>
<P>
Later in the day, soon after school was dismissed, the suspect drove to the 
house where Delgado was standing with a group of friends waiting for a ride 
home and shot him, she said. 
</P>
<P>
Although police arrested three adults in connection with the shooting, charges 
have been filed only against the juvenile, Rodela said. He was charged with 
murder in Inglewood Juvenile Court. 
</P>
