NEWSWIRE: NAMES IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Linebacker Mickey Pruitt of the Chicago Bears broke his left hand in a fight 
with guard Mark Bortz during practice. Pruitt, a special teams player, had his 
hand put in a cast but is expected to play Sunday against the Broncos at 
Denver. Bortz was unhurt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
