<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jimmy Ward, popular right wing with the defunct Montreal Maroons of the NHL, 
died of cancer in Portland, Ore. 
</P>
<P>
He was 84. 
</P>
<P>
Ward, a 12-year NHL veteran, was a member of the Maroons' Stanley Cup champions 
in 1935. He retired in 1939 after suffering a shoulder injury while playing 
with the Canadiens. 
</P>
<P>
Ward scored 274 points and had 147 goals. 
</P>
<P>
A memorial service will be held Sunday at Ross Memorial in Portland. In lieu of 
flowers, the family asks that a donation be sent to Hospice, 6040 N. Cutter 
Circle, Suite 309, Portland, Ore. 97217. Hospice is an organization of visiting 
nurses who help terminally ill patients suffering from cancer. 
</P>
