<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL REPORT / WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
RAIDERS; 
</P>
<P>
DOLPHIN DEFENSE HAS IMPROVED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS BAKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Defensive end Jeff Cross, leader of the Miami Pound Machine with 10 sacks, said 
the Dolphin defense has improved since last season because of consistency. 
</P>
<P>
"We're just playing a straight-up defense," Cross said. 
</P>
<P>
"We're just lining up and getting after people." 
</P>
<P>
So how will the Raiders attack the Dolphin defense Monday night in Miami? 
</P>
<P>
"They're a very good football team, and they're playing extremely well," Raider 
quarterback Jay Schroeder said of the Dolphins. "But I have confidence that the 
guys up front are going to be able to block them." 
</P>
<P>
Injuries: Raider safety Eddie Anderson (knee injury), receiver Jamie Holland 
(foot) and defensive tackle Bill Pickel (back) are listed as probable. Dolphin 
safety Bobby Harden (hamstring) is doubtful; fullbacks Marc Logan (knee) and 
Tony Paige (knee), and defensive end Karl Wilson (ankle) are questionable; 
linebacker John Offerdahl (toe) is probable. CHRIS BAKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
