<P>
MAN ACCUSED OF KIDNAPING, RAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 31-year-old Ventura County man was arrested on suspicion of kidnaping and 
raping a woman he promised a job as a baby-sitter, authorities said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Douglas Ray Kaufman was being held in the Ventura County Jail on $20,000 bail, 
a jail spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The 35-year-old woman, who is a transient, told police that she met a man 
Monday when she was at the intersection of Yerba Buena Road and the Pacific 
Coast Highway, Ventura County Sheriff's Sgt. John Fitzgerald said. 
</P>
<P>
The man, who pulled over to the side of the road, said he needed a baby-sitter 
and asked if she needed work, Fitzgerald said. They arranged for him to pick 
her up the next day, Fitzgerald said. 
</P>
<P>
The man drove the woman to his house on Cotharin Road south of Thousand Oaks 
about 6 p.m. Tuesday, Fitzgerald said. The woman said the man then bound her 
hands behind her back and raped her, Fitzgerald said. 
</P>
<P>
The woman said the man later put her back in the car, drove her to a shed about 
a quarter of a mile away and left her there, Fitzgerald said. 
</P>
<P>
The woman later freed herself and made her way to a restaurant about 7:30 a.m. 
Wednesday. People there called the Sheriff's Department and she then led 
deputies to a house where Kaufman was arrested. CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
