<P>
PLANNING PANEL SEEKS MEMBERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four of five positions are open on the Thousand Oaks Planning Commission. 
</P>
<P>
The city clerk's office will accept applications for the positions until Nov. 
30. Accepted applicants, who must be residents of the city and registered 
voters, will be nominated by a council member and approved by the full council, 
said City Clerk Nancy Dillon. 
</P>
<P>
The five-person commission meets every Monday night, discussing the city 
General Plan, which addresses land use and housing issues. 
</P>
