<HEADLINE>
<P>
FEMALE COMEDY REVUE PERFORMS TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Ladies of the Evening, an all-women, stand-up comedy revue, will take the 
stage tonight at the Westwood Club, 17394 West Bernardo Drive, to poke fun at 
relationships, family and life's little frustrations. 
</P>
<P>
The group includes Karen Rontowski, a recent runner-up in the "Funniest Person 
in San Diego" contest; Kathy Foley, a flight attendant who bills herself as 
"the air bag," and Anita Milner, a 54-year-old Escondido attorney who uses 
comedy as a release from job stress. The evening also includes Comedy Store 
worker Lorian Elbert, Jere Evans who performs regularly in Los Angeles, and 
desktop publisher Betsy Mill. 
</P>
<P>
Ticket information for the 8 p.m. show is available by calling 485-6300. No 
children under 16 will be admitted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
