<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Lanie Jones and Bob Schwartz 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STAMP ART: Reproductions of the painting on the annual federal duck-hunting 
stamp are said to net $1 million or more for the artist (E1). 
</P>
<P>
But that doesn't hold true for the scores of state hunting stamps, according to 
Dave Chapple of Irvine, onetime Rams punter whose paintings are on six state 
stamps. "You have to give them the painting free, and some states make you 
publish the stamps too, and that's around $15,000," Chapple says. "If you've 
got time to . . . promote your pictures, you can do OK. I'd rather just sell 
the original." Lanie Jones and Bob Schwartz 
</P>
</TEXT>
