<HEADLINE>
<P>
DALLAS FIRM ACQUIRES TRANSAMERICA UNIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DALLAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Associates Corp. of North America has acquired Transamerica Fleet Leasing Corp. 
from Transamerica Commercial Finance Corp. for an undisclosed sum. 
</P>
<P>
Associates, a unit of Ford Motor Co., assumes lease and management 
responsibilities for about 9,300 autos and light trucks previously owned or 
managed by Transamerica Commercial. 
</P>
<P>
Associates now has more than 66,000 autos and light trucks under lease and 
management nationwide. 
</P>
<P>
Chicago-based Transamerica Commercial is a wholly owned subsidiary of 
Transamerica Corp. of San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
"The acquisition of the Transamerica automotive portfolio is a significant 
addition to Associates Leasing," said Chairman Reece A. Overcash Jr. 
"Transamerica Fleet Leasing has a reputation for providing high standards of 
service to its clients, and we intend to maintain that quality." 
</P>
<P>
Robert A. Watson, president of Transamerica Commercial Finance Corp., said the 
sale is a continaution fo his company's strategy of focusing its commercial 
financing activities on inventory financing, insurance premium financing and 
specialized asset-based lending. 
</P>
<P>
Associates, with assets of more than $16 billion, provides consumer finance, 
specialized commercial finance and leasing, and insurance. It manages financial 
assets of Ford subsidiaries in the United States, Britain, Japan and Canada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
