<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOEING GETS ORDERS FOR FIVE MORE 737S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEATTLE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ansett Worldwide Aviation Services has ordered five more Boeing 737-500 
airliners, worth about $150 million, Boeing Commercial Airplane Group 
announced. 
</P>
<P>
Two of the five aircraft have already been delivered, one to Europe Aero 
Service, a French carrier, and the other to Balkan Bulgarian Airlines. 
</P>
<P>
Ansett Worldwide, an Australian leasing company, has now announced orders for 
86 Boeing jetliners, including 55 737s, 22 757s and nine 767s. 
</P>
<P>
For the year, Boeing has announced orders for 460 aircraft, with an approximate 
value of $41.5 billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
