<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
DOLPHINS SIGN 2 PASS RECEIVERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MIAMI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Miami Dolphins placed backup receiver Fred Banks on injured reserve today 
and signed two free agent receivers -- Dennis McKinnon and James Pruitt. 
</P>
<P>
Banks will miss at least four games after fracturing his left foot in practice 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
He is the second receiver to go on injured reserve this week; starter Mark 
Clayton suffered a knee injury in last Sunday's victory over the New York Jets 
and will also be sidelined for at least a month. 
</P>
<P>
Pruitt played with the Dolphins in 1986-88 before signing with the Indianapolis 
Colts as a Plan B free agent. The Colts waived him on Sept. 17. 
</P>
<P>
McKinnon played with the Chicago Bears from 1983 to 1989. He went to Dallas as 
a Plan B free agent and caught 14 passes for 172 yards this season before the 
Cowboys waived him Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Banks has caught 13 passes for 131 yards this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
