<P>
GRIFFIN MAKES IT TO BOXING FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOMBAY, India 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
American Eric Griffin, the world amateur light flyweight champion, advanced to 
the finals of the World Cup boxing tournament today by stopping Zoram Thanga of 
India in the third round. 
</P>
<P>
Griffin will fight Orlando Ascensio for the title since the Cuban advanced by 
outpointing Dharmendra Yadav of India, 12-11. 
</P>
<P>
Ascensio was one of four Cubans to move into the finals. 
</P>
<P>
Juan Lemus stopped Ole Klemetsen of Norway in the third round of their light 
middleweight bout; Enrique Carrion beat Fred Muteweta of Uganda on points in 
their bantamweight match, and Roberto Balado won in the super-heavyweight 
division when Vernon Linklater of Canada quit in the second round. 
</P>
<P>
In the other semifinal in the light middleweight section, Canadian Raymond 
Downey outpointed George Onyango of Kenya 17-21. 
</P>
