<TEXT>
<P>
The contents of Ava Gardner's London apartment where she lived as a recluse 
until her death last January -- including about 75 pairs of shoes -- will be 
auctioned off next week. 
</P>
<P>
Sotheby's auction house said today that it expects to raise about $1.2 million 
from the sale. 
</P>
<P>
The Hollywood star lived in London for 17 years. The apartment's contents 
reveal her liking for Oriental antiques and wall hangings as well an her 
extravagant taste in shoes. 
